definition:
A *Gaussian sum* is a sum of the form $$\begin{aligned}
S \;:=\; \sum_{j=0}^{n-1}e^{\frac{2\pi i}{n}j^2}\end{aligned}$$ where
$n$ is a positive integer.\
The explicit value of $S$ may be found by using the Cauchy residue
theorem for determining the contour integral
$$I \;:=\; \oint_\gamma\frac{e^{\frac{2\pi i}{n}z^2}}{1\!-\!e^{2\pi iz}}\,dz$$
where $\gamma$ goes once anticlockwise round the set of the
$1,\,2,\,\ldots,\,\lfloor\frac{n-1}{2}\rfloor$ of the integrand
($\gamma$ is formed by a rectangle where two segments are replaced by
arcs of half-circle).

